Name: Meter
Description: The base unit of length in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Kilometer
Description: A unit of length equal to 1,000 meters.

Name: Centimeter
Description: A unit of length equal to one hundredth of a meter.

Name: Kilogram
Description: The base unit of mass in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Gram
Description: A unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a kilogram.

Name: Ton
Description: A unit of mass equal to 1,000 kilograms.

Name: Second
Description: The base unit of time in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Minute
Description: A unit of time equal to 60 seconds.

Name: Hour
Description: A unit of time equal to 3,600 seconds or 60 minutes.

Name: Kelvin
Description: The base unit of temperature in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Celsius
Description: A scale and unit of measurement for temperature.

Name: Liter
Description: A unit of volume equal to 1 cubic decimeter.

Name: Milliliter
Description: A unit of volume equal to one thousandth of a liter.

Name: Square Meter
Description: The base unit of area in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Square Kilometer
Description: A unit of area equal to 1,000,000 square meters.

Name: Meter per Second
Description: The base unit of speed in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Hertz
Description: The base unit of frequency in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Pascal
Description: The base unit of pressure in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Joule
Description: The base unit of energy in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Watt
Description: The base unit of power in the International System of Units (SI).

Name: Byte
Description: The base unit of digital information.

Name: Kilobyte
Description: A unit of digital information equal to 1,024 bytes.
